  "text": "Daptomycin plasma and urine concentrations were analyzed using reverse-phase high-performance liquid chromatography with UV detection at 220 nm over a range of concentrations from 2 to 100 g/ml (7). The intrarun percent coefficients of variation for the low-quality control of 4 g/ml and the highquality control of 80 g/ml were 6.20% and 4.69%, respectively. The interrun percent coefficients of variation were 5.74% and 2.56%, respectively. The correlation coefficient for each calibration curve was greater than 0.999. Daptomycin protein binding was evaluated as previously described [CITATION_1] .",
